verses.text: O give \w thanks|strong="H3034"\w* unto the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*; \w call|strong="H7121"\w* upon his \w name|strong="H8034"\w*: make \w known|strong="H3045"\w* his \w deeds|strong="H5949"\w* among the \w people|strong="H5971"\w*.
\w Sing|strong="H7891"\w* unto him, sing \w psalms|strong="H2167"\w* unto him: \w talk|strong="H7878"\w* ye of all his wondrous \w works|strong="H6381"\w*.

\w Glory|strong="H1984"\w* ye in his \w holy|strong="H6944"\w* \w name|strong="H8034"\w*: let the \w heart|strong="H3820"\w* of them \w rejoice|strong="H8055"\w* that \w seek|strong="H1245"\w* the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*.
\w Seek|strong="H1875"\w* the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*, and his \w strength|strong="H5797"\w*: \w seek|strong="H1245"\w* his \w face|strong="H6440"\w* \w evermore|strong="H8548"\w*.

\w Remember|strong="H2142"\w* his marvellous \w works|strong="H6381"\w* that he hath \w done|strong="H6213"\w*; his \w wonders|strong="H4159"\w*, and the \w judgments|strong="H4941"\w* of his \w mouth|strong="H6310"\w*;
O ye \w seed|strong="H2233"\w* of \w Abraham|strong="H0085"\w* his \w servant|strong="H5650"\w*, ye \w children|strong="H1121"\w* of \w Jacob|strong="H3290"\w* his \w chosen|strong="H0972"\w*.
He \add is\add* the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* our \w God|strong="H0430"\w*: his \w judgments|strong="H4941"\w* \add are\add* in all the \w earth|strong="H0776"\w*.

He hath \w remembered|strong="H2142"\w* his \w covenant|strong="H1285"\w* for \w ever|strong="H5769"\w*, the \w word|strong="H1697"\w* \add which\add* he \w commanded|strong="H6680"\w* to a \w thousand|strong="H0505"\w* \w generations|strong="H1755"\w*.
Which \add covenant\add* he \w made|strong="H3772"\w* with \w Abraham|strong="H0085"\w*, and his \w oath|strong="H7621"\w* unto \w Isaac|strong="H3446"\w*;

And \w confirmed|strong="H5975"\w* the same unto \w Jacob|strong="H3290"\w* for a \w law|strong="H2706"\w*, \add and\add* to \w Israel|strong="H3478"\w* \add for\add* an \w everlasting|strong="H5769"\w* \w covenant|strong="H1285"\w*:

\w Saying|strong="H0559"\w*, Unto thee will I \w give|strong="H5414"\w* the \w land|strong="H0776"\w* of \w Canaan|strong="H3667"\w*, the \w lot|strong="H2256"\w* of your \w inheritance|strong="H5159"\w*:\f + \fr 105.11 \ft lot: Heb. cord\f*
When they were \add but\add* a few \w men|strong="H4962"\w* in \w number|strong="H4557"\w*; yea, very \w few|strong="H4592"\w*, and \w strangers|strong="H1481"\w* in it.
When they \w went|strong="H1980"\w* from one \w nation|strong="H1471"\w* to another, from \add one\add* \w kingdom|strong="H4467"\w* to \w another|strong="H0312"\w* \w people|strong="H5971"\w*;
He \w suffered|strong="H3240"\w* no \w man|strong="H0120"\w* to do them \w wrong|strong="H6231"\w*: yea, he \w reproved|strong="H3198"\w* \w kings|strong="H4428"\w* for their sakes;
\add Saying\add*, \w Touch|strong="H5060"\w* not mine \w anointed|strong="H4899"\w*, and do my \w prophets|strong="H5030"\w* no \w harm|strong="H7489"\w*.

Moreover he \w called|strong="H7121"\w* for a \w famine|strong="H7458"\w* upon the \w land|strong="H0776"\w*: he \w brake|strong="H7665"\w* the whole \w staff|strong="H4294"\w* of \w bread|strong="H3899"\w*.

He \w sent|strong="H7971"\w* a \w man|strong="H0376"\w* \w before|strong="H6440"\w* them, \add even\add* \w Joseph|strong="H3130"\w*, \add who\add* was \w sold|strong="H4376"\w* for a \w servant|strong="H5650"\w*:

Whose \w feet|strong="H7272"\w* they \w hurt|strong="H6031"\w* with \w fetters|strong="H3525"\w*: \w he|strong="H5315"\w* was \w laid|strong="H0935"\w* in \w iron|strong="H1270"\w*:\f + \fr 105.18 \ft he…: Heb. his soul came into iron\f*

Until the \w time|strong="H6256"\w* that his \w word|strong="H1697"\w* \w came|strong="H0935"\w*: the \w word|strong="H0565"\w* of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* \w tried|strong="H6884"\w* him.

The \w king|strong="H4428"\w* \w sent|strong="H7971"\w* and \w loosed|strong="H5425"\w* him; \add even\add* the \w ruler|strong="H4910"\w* of the \w people|strong="H5971"\w*, and let him go \w free|strong="H6605"\w*.

He \w made|strong="H7760"\w* him \w lord|strong="H0113"\w* of his \w house|strong="H1004"\w*, and \w ruler|strong="H4910"\w* of all his \w substance|strong="H7075"\w*:\f + \fr 105.21 \ft substance: Heb. possession\f*
To \w bind|strong="H0631"\w* his \w princes|strong="H8269"\w* at his \w pleasure|strong="H5315"\w*; and teach his \w senators|strong="H2205"\w* \w wisdom|strong="H2449"\w*.

\w Israel|strong="H3478"\w* also \w came|strong="H0935"\w* into \w Egypt|strong="H4714"\w*; and \w Jacob|strong="H3290"\w* \w sojourned|strong="H1481"\w* in the \w land|strong="H0776"\w* of \w Ham|strong="H2526"\w*.
And he \w increased|strong="H6509"\w* his \w people|strong="H5971"\w* \w greatly|strong="H3966"\w*; and made them \w stronger|strong="H6105"\w* than their \w enemies|strong="H6862"\w*.

He \w turned|strong="H2015"\w* their \w heart|strong="H3820"\w* to \w hate|strong="H8130"\w* his \w people|strong="H5971"\w*, to deal \w subtilly|strong="H5230"\w* with his \w servants|strong="H5650"\w*.
He \w sent|strong="H7971"\w* \w Moses|strong="H4872"\w* his \w servant|strong="H5650"\w*; \add and\add* \w Aaron|strong="H0175"\w* whom he had \w chosen|strong="H0977"\w*.

They \w shewed|strong="H7760"\w* his \w signs|strong="H0226"\w* among them, and \w wonders|strong="H4159"\w* in the \w land|strong="H0776"\w* of \w Ham|strong="H2526"\w*.\f + \fr 105.27 \ft his…: Heb. words of his signs\f*
He \w sent|strong="H7971"\w* \w darkness|strong="H2822"\w*, and made it \w dark|strong="H2821"\w*; and they \w rebelled|strong="H4784"\w* not against his \w word|strong="H1697"\w*.
He \w turned|strong="H2015"\w* their \w waters|strong="H4325"\w* into \w blood|strong="H1818"\w*, and \w slew|strong="H4191"\w* their \w fish|strong="H1710"\w*.

Their \w land|strong="H0776"\w* brought \w forth|strong="H8317"\w* \w frogs|strong="H6854"\w* in \w abundance|strong="H8317"\w*, in the \w chambers|strong="H2315"\w* of their \w kings|strong="H4428"\w*.
He \w spake|strong="H0559"\w*, and there \w came|strong="H0935"\w* divers sorts of \w flies|strong="H6157"\w*, \add and\add* \w lice|strong="H3654"\w* in all their \w coasts|strong="H1366"\w*.

He \w gave|strong="H5414"\w* them \w hail|strong="H1259"\w* for \w rain|strong="H1653"\w*, \add and\add* \w flaming|strong="H3852"\w* \w fire|strong="H0784"\w* in their \w land|strong="H0776"\w*.\f + \fr 105.32 \ft them…: Heb. their rain hail\f*

He \w smote|strong="H5221"\w* their \w vines|strong="H1612"\w* also and their fig \w trees|strong="H8384"\w*; and \w brake|strong="H7665"\w* the \w trees|strong="H6086"\w* of their \w coasts|strong="H1366"\w*.
He \w spake|strong="H0559"\w*, and the \w locusts|strong="H0697"\w* \w came|strong="H0935"\w*, and \w caterpillers|strong="H3218"\w*, and that without \w number|strong="H4557"\w*,

And did eat \w up|strong="H0398"\w* all the \w herbs|strong="H6212"\w* in their \w land|strong="H0776"\w*, and \w devoured|strong="H0398"\w* the \w fruit|strong="H6529"\w* of their \w ground|strong="H0127"\w*.
He \w smote|strong="H5221"\w* also all the \w firstborn|strong="H1060"\w* in their \w land|strong="H0776"\w*, the \w chief|strong="H7225"\w* of all their \w strength|strong="H0202"\w*.

He brought them \w forth|strong="H3318"\w* also with \w silver|strong="H3701"\w* and \w gold|strong="H2091"\w*: and \add there was\add* not one \w feeble|strong="H3782"\w* \add person\add* among their \w tribes|strong="H7626"\w*.
\w Egypt|strong="H4714"\w* was \w glad|strong="H8055"\w* when they \w departed|strong="H3318"\w*: for the \w fear|strong="H6343"\w* of them \w fell|strong="H5307"\w* upon them.
He \w spread|strong="H6566"\w* a \w cloud|strong="H6051"\w* for a \w covering|strong="H4539"\w*; and \w fire|strong="H0784"\w* to give \w light|strong="H0215"\w* in the \w night|strong="H3915"\w*.

\add The people\add* \w asked|strong="H7592"\w*, and he \w brought|strong="H0935"\w* \w quails|strong="H7958"\w*, and \w satisfied|strong="H7646"\w* them with the \w bread|strong="H3899"\w* of \w heaven|strong="H8064"\w*.

He \w opened|strong="H6605"\w* the \w rock|strong="H6697"\w*, and the \w waters|strong="H4325"\w* gushed \w out|strong="H2100"\w*; they \w ran|strong="H1980"\w* in the dry \w places|strong="H6723"\w* \add like\add* a \w river|strong="H5104"\w*.
For he \w remembered|strong="H2142"\w* his \w holy|strong="H6944"\w* \w promise|strong="H1697"\w*, \add and\add* \w Abraham|strong="H0085"\w* his \w servant|strong="H5650"\w*.

And he brought \w forth|strong="H3318"\w* his \w people|strong="H5971"\w* with \w joy|strong="H8342"\w*, \add and\add* his \w chosen|strong="H0972"\w* with \w gladness|strong="H7440"\w*:\f + \fr 105.43 \ft gladness: Heb. singing\f*

And \w gave|strong="H5414"\w* them the \w lands|strong="H0776"\w* of the \w heathen|strong="H1471"\w*: and they \w inherited|strong="H3423"\w* the \w labour|strong="H5999"\w* of the \w people|strong="H3816"\w*;

That they might \w observe|strong="H8104"\w* his \w statutes|strong="H2706"\w*, and \w keep|strong="H5341"\w* his \w laws|strong="H8451"\w*. \w Praise|strong="H1984"\w* ye the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3050"\+w*\nd*.\f + \fr 105.45 \ft Praise…: Heb. Hallelujah\f*
